<subSubSection id="49C942EEFFF5392DEBD2C114FD675C43" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="016C1165FFF5392DEBD2C114FEAA5D77" blockId="91.[227,341,1575,1601]" box="[227,341,1575,1601]" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">
<heading id="5A24A609FFF5392DEBD2C114FEAA5D77" bold="true" box="[227,341,1575,1601]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" reason="3">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FFF5392DEBD2C114FEAA5D77" bold="true" box="[227,341,1575,1601]" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="016C1165FFF5392DEBD2C164FD675C43" blockId="91.[225,1437,1623,1910]" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">
The otoliths of “ 
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FFF5392DEA91C16BFE505D44" box="[416,431,1624,1650]" italics="true" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">S</emphasis>
.” 
<taxonomicName id="C6D36AE6FFF5392DEAF8C164FDB75D47" authorityName="Koken" authorityYear="1888" box="[457,584,1623,1649]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sciaenidae" genus="Sciaena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="intermedia">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FFF5392DEAF8C164FDB75D47" box="[457,584,1623,1649]" italics="true" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">intermedia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and “ 
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FFF5392DE9BAC16BFD655D44" box="[651,666,1624,1650]" italics="true" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">S</emphasis>
.” 
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FFF5392DE985C164FCF15D47" box="[692,782,1623,1649]" italics="true" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">livesayi</emphasis>
both have a long cauda that strongly bends at about onethird of its length, a similar ostial length and a similar inner face convexity. However, “ 
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FFF5392DEFFBC14EFB265DA1" box="[1226,1241,1661,1687]" italics="true" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">S</emphasis>
.” 
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FFF5392DEFC2C14FFAB25DA0" box="[1267,1357,1660,1686]" italics="true" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">livesayi</emphasis>
can be distinguished from “ 
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FFF5392DEAE2C191FE1D5D8A" box="[467,482,1698,1724]" italics="true" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">S</emphasis>
.” 
<taxonomicName id="C6D36AE6FFF5392DEACCC191FD835D8A" authorityName="Koken" authorityYear="1888" box="[509,636,1698,1724]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sciaenidae" genus="Sciaena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="intermedia">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FFF5392DEACCC191FD835D8A" box="[509,636,1698,1724]" italics="true" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">intermedia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having a more antero-posteriorly compressed shape, mostly with a caudal tip directed more anteriorly, and by the much wider ostium, whose ventral part is not constricted on the crista inferior. 
<bibRefCitation id="65426C94FFF5392DEAD0C1DFFD1C5C30" author="Ebersole" box="[481,739,1772,1798]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Ebersole" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" refId="ref53603" refString="Ebersole J. A., Cicimurri D. J. &amp; Stringer G. L. 2019. Taxonomy and biostratigraphy of the elasmobranchs and bony fishes (Chondrichthyes and Osteichthyes) of the lower - to - middle Eocene (Ypresian to Bartonian) Claiborne Group in Alabama, USA, including an analysis of otoliths. European Journal of" type="book" year="2019">
Ebersole 
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FFF5392DE963C1DEFD7A5C30" box="[594,645,1772,1798]" italics="true" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">et al</emphasis>
. (2019)
</bibRefCitation>
hypothesized a close relationship between “ 
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FFF5392DEFC3C1DFFAFE5C30" box="[1266,1281,1772,1798]" italics="true" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">S</emphasis>
.” 
<taxonomicName id="C6D36AE6FFF5392DEE2CC1DFFA635C30" authorityName="Koken" authorityYear="1888" box="[1309,1436,1772,1798]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sciaenidae" genus="Sciaena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="intermedia">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FFF5392DEE2CC1DFFA635C30" box="[1309,1436,1772,1798]" italics="true" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">intermedia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="C6D36AE6FFF5392DEA26C022FE1B5C1D" baseAuthorityName="Dante &amp; Frizzell" baseAuthorityYear="1965" box="[279,484,1809,1835]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sciaenidae" genus="Sciaena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pseudoradians">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FFF5392DEA26C022FE1B5C1D" box="[279,484,1809,1835]" italics="true" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">S. pseudoradians</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and even with 
<taxonomicName id="C6D36AE6FFF5392DE998C022FCF35C1D" authorityName="Dante &amp; Frizzell" authorityYear="1965" box="[681,780,1809,1835]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sciaenidae" genus="Jefitchia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FFF5392DE998C022FCF35C1D" box="[681,780,1809,1835]" italics="true" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">Jefitchia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It seems to us that otoliths of “ 
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FFF5392DEFA9C022FB585C1D" box="[1176,1191,1809,1835]" italics="true" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">S</emphasis>
.” 
<taxonomicName id="C6D36AE6FFF5392DEFF4C022FABB5C1D" authorityName="Koken" authorityYear="1888" box="[1221,1348,1809,1835]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sciaenidae" genus="Sciaena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="intermedia">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FFF5392DEFF4C022FABB5C1D" box="[1221,1348,1809,1835]" italics="true" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">intermedia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
indeed resemble those of 
<taxonomicName id="C6D36AE6FFF5392DEA8CC005FD775C66" baseAuthorityName="Dante &amp; Frizzell" baseAuthorityYear="1965" box="[445,648,1846,1872]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sciaenidae" genus="Sciaena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pseudoradians">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FFF5392DEA8CC005FD775C66" box="[445,648,1846,1872]" italics="true" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">S. pseudoradians</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Supplementary file 1), but 
<taxonomicName id="C6D36AE6FFF5392DE8E6C005FBC55C66" authorityName="Dante &amp; Frizzell" authorityYear="1965" box="[983,1082,1846,1872]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sciaenidae" genus="Jefitchia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FFF5392DE8E6C005FBC55C66" box="[983,1082,1846,1872]" italics="true" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">Jefitchia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="C6D36AE6FFF5392DEF7AC004FB235C66" authorityName="Dante &amp; Frizzell" authorityYear="1965" box="[1099,1244,1846,1872]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sciaenidae" genus="Jefitchia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="copelandi">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FFF5392DEF7AC004FB235C66" box="[1099,1244,1846,1872]" italics="true" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">J. copelandi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) is very distinct and likely represent a different clade.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
